line: Okay.

speaker: Michael
line: Okay.

line: So, how you been?

speaker: Jan
line: Been good.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Good.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: Good.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Yeah.

speaker: Jan
line: Sorry to drop by unexpectedly. I uh, I tried calling, but I kept getting voice mail.

speaker: Michael
line: Weird. Yeah, I didn't get both of your messages.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: So, um, Michael needs us in the conference room.

speaker: Karen
line: 'Cause of Jan again?

line: Hey, uh, before I leave tonight, would you mind making a half a dozen copies of Jim's and my sales reports for our interviews tomorrow?

speaker: Pam
line: Uh, sure.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: Thanks.

speaker: Pam
line: I really hope you get the job.

speaker: Karen
line: Thanks.

speaker: Michael
line: Hmm.

speaker: Jan
line: To kinda clear my mind.

speaker: Michael
line: Sound good. Sounds fun.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: It was. Yeah, it was good.  I think I'll just get right to the point, you know? Um, I, I feel good about myself for the first time in a really long time.

speaker: Michael
line: Hmm..

line: I've made some big changes in my life and... I miss you. I want us to get back together.

speaker: Michael
line: Would you excuse me for a second?

speaker: Jan
line: Ohh...

line: Defcon twenty. She wants to get back together.

speaker: Phyllis
line: What are you gonna do?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: I don't know, that's why you're here, help me. Please...

line: Do you want to get back together with her?

line: No, no. What do I do?

line: What if she makes me?

speaker: Pam
line: This was a terrible relationship. You were not happy when you were with her.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: I wasn't.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: You're so much happier now. Just go in there and be strong.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: You're right. You're absolutely right. I'm gonna go in there and tell her that we can't be together.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: Right.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Wow.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: Do it.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: I'm in a very good place right now. Thank you.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jim
line: Yeah, bigger actually.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: That's crazy!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jim
line: Mm-hm.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: Wow!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: Oh my God. Can you believe that?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jim
line: Unbelievable.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: Wow!

speaker: Jim
line: She could put the cup right there.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: I know!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: So...  there are a lot of things that I would like to do differently.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Yeah.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: I feel like, when we first got together, that I had a problem with my priorities.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: First got priorities.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: And if we could talk about a way to approach a possible reconciliation...

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Let's get back together.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Okay, everyone, listen up!  Time to begin the interview process!  Andrew Bernard.

speaker: Andy
line: Saving the best for first!

speaker: Karen
line: All right, you guys. See you later, wish us luck!

speaker: Dwight
line: No! Hey, hey, hey, hey! Do not wish them luck. Do not wish them luck. All luck must be wished unto Michael.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)

line: Good luck, you guys!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: What did I say!?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: Good luck.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jim
line: Thanks.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: I am going to begin this process with a simple test of intelligence and mental dexterity. What is the best color?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Andy
line: White, because it contains all other colors.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Wrong. Black. It is the most dominant. How do you make a table?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Andy
line: You make a chair, but you don't sit on it.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: What is the capital of Maine?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Andy
line: The capital of Maine is Montpelier, Vermont, which is near Ithaca, New York, where I went to Cornell.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Okay, also, moratorium on Cornell talk. Don't wanna hear about it. Forget your personal history, and learn the history of this company.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Andy
line: Should not be a problem. I minored in history in the Ivy League school which I attended.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: You're not off to a very good start, Bernard.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Andy
line: I agree. But in another way, I am off to a very good start, wouldn't you say?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Time! No, you failed.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Andy
line: Damn it!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: This interview is over. I'll let you know.

speaker: Karen
line: Hey, thank you so much for driving me down for my interview.

speaker: Jim
line: Totally, no problem. What are you interviewing for, by the way, my assistant? Or...

speaker: Karen
line: Oh, you know I'm gonna have a congratulations Karen party um, tomorrow night at my friend's house.

speaker: Jim
line: Oh wow, that sounds like fun. Is your friend named Karen too? What did she accomplish?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: No, I'm sorry I should have been clearer. It's for me.

speaker: Jim
line: Oh...

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: 'Cause I'm going to get the job.

speaker: Michael
line: Remarkable.

speaker: Jan
line: Thanks.

line: Wait, wait. Check one more time.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)

line: Oh, okay.

speaker: Michael
line: Very good

line: Well, I um, I have to get back, but I will see you in New York tomorrow, right?

line: Yes, indeed.

speaker: Jan
line: Good luck with your interview.  Bye.

line: So, I guess we're getting back together.

line: What happened?

speaker: Jim
line: Oh, I dunno, how about the U.N.?

speaker: Karen
line: How often do you come here?

speaker: Jim
line: Um, everytime my sixth grade class has a field trip.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: I think you'll really enjoy this, adult Jim.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jim
line: Yeah, we went to the Spotted Pig for dinner. It's in the Village. Uh, Karen knew it. And then we second acted Spamalot. That's when you sneak in at intermission with all the smokers. And then we went to a bar that used to be a church. Oh and at this one bar, I swear I saw Lorne Michaels.

speaker: Karen
line: That wasn't him.

speaker: Karen
line: So what's going to happen to us when I get this job?

speaker: Jim
line: Oh do you mean when I get the job?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jim
line: You mean Kevin?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: Exactly. But you get it, right? Can't stay there.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jim
line: Yeah, I do. C'mon.

speaker: Michael
line: How are you guys doing? Need anything?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: Uh, no, we're good. Thanks.

speaker: Michael
line: I have been here a bunch of times, so I know where everything is, know everybody's names. If you need to know somebody's name, just ask me.

speaker: Jim
line: Who's that?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jim
line: Beardy?

speaker: Michael
line: Mm-hmm.

speaker: Jim
line: I'm gonna introduce myself.

speaker: Michael
line: No, no, no, just... that's not his real name. That's just what I call him, so...

speaker: Dwight
line: Michael is gone.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Andy
line: Hail to the chief!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: My first order of business: make Andrew Bernard my number two.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Andy
line: My first order of business: accept.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: As if you had a choice.  Duh.  Opportunity of a lifetime.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Hey! Hunter! Wha's up my brutha? This is Hunter, secretary extraordinaire.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Jan in yet?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Could you give her a message for me, when she gets in?

speaker: Michael
line: Just say, "I want to squeeze them." It's code. She'll know what it means.

speaker: Michael
line: Oh, and Hunter? Could you tell her,  "Brbrbrbrbr!" also?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: You showed great leadership potential at the coal walk. Even if you did follow it with that embarrassing personal confession.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: Thank you.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: I had to make Andy my number two. It's political, complicated, you wouldn't understand. I want you... to be Assistant Regional Manager.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: Really?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Well, in a sense. Although, publicly I am going to retain the Assistant Regional Manager position.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: You will be your own assistant.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Correct, I need someone I can trust. But I would also like the title... to be secretly applied to you. Just stripped of its pomp and frills.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: Mm-hmm.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Do you accept?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: Absolutely, I do.

speaker: Michael
line: Hello, hello!

speaker: David Wallace
line: Michael, good to see you!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Good to see you. Here are the post-merger performance stats that you asked for.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: Oh, great. I've been meaning to thank you by the way. You didn't lose a single customer during the merger, and you still managed to trim the budget? That is nice work.  So, let me ask you a question right off the bat. What do you think are your greatest strengths as a manager?

speaker: Michael
line: Why don't I tell you what my greatest weaknesses are? I work too hard. I care too much. And sometimes I can be too invested in my job.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: Okay. And your strengths?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Well, my weaknesses are actually... strengths.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: Oh. Yes. Very good.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Thank you.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: Very good.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Phyllis
line: Dwight is our new boss.

speaker: Oscar
line: Oh, Michael's not going anywhere.

speaker: Pam
line: Then who do you think will get the job?

speaker: Kevin
line: Karen. She looks corporate. Those little pants suits.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Phyllis
line: I think it's gonna be Michael.

speaker: Oscar
line: Do you really think he's qualified for that job?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Phyllis
line: No, but he wasn't qualified for the job he has now, and he got that one.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Oscar
line: Mm. Yeah.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Listen up! Come to the center of the room, please. This...  is a Schrute Buck. When you have done something good, you will receive one Schrute Buck. One thousand Schrute Bucks... equals an extra five minutes for lunch.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: What is the cash value of a Schrute Buck?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Excellent question, Pam. 1/100th of a cent.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Just... zip your lid! Another announcement. Michael wasted an enormous amount of the group's time and patience with non-work related ethnic celebrations and parades of soft-minded dogoodedness. No longer. No more meetings!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Stanley
line: Amen.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Instead, today I will begin my first lecture in a long series of lectures designed to increase your knowledge on the world of paper.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Kevin
line: Do we have to?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Yes! Michael is gone. There's a new sheriff here in these offices, and his name is "me." Conference room! Ten seconds! All of you!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: What do you think we could be doing better?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: I've never been a big fan of the name Dunder Mifflin. I was thinking we could name the company something like, "Paper Great. Where great paper is our passion. We're GRRRRRRRRRREAT!" I don't know, could be good. Or, uh, "Super Duper Paper. It's super duper." I don't know, something like that.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: Okay!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Okay.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: Thanks for comin' in, Michael.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Thank you.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: It is always a treat when our paths cross.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: You're back together.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Yes. And I am very excited about the prospect of working under her... or on top of her.  Mm, that's not sexual, just... we're all professionals.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: Okay, uh. Well, I thought it was clear in the description, the position... the job you're applying for... is Jan's job.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: I don't understand. So, we're gonna tag team it?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: No, we're letting Jan go.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Kevin
line: Trees.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Trees! And where do trees grow?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Kevin
line: Forest.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Soil. Right. We have, in front of you here, seven different types of Pennsylvania top soil. Now, what would you say... is the most important element in the production of above ground leafy growth? Probably phosphorus, right?  Wrong! It's nitrogen! Absorb this information. Good! Now, let us discuss precipitation. Stanley! When rainfall occurs, does it usually fall in a liquid, solid, or gaseous... state?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Stanley
line: Liquid.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Very good! You have earned one Schrute Buck.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Stanley
line: I don't want it.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Then you have been deducted 50 Schrute Bucks!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Stanley
line: Make it 100.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: We--- Don't you wanna earn Schrute Bucks?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Stanley
line: No. In fact, I'll give you a billion Stanley Nickels if you never talk to me again.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: What's the ratio of Stanley Nickels to Schrute Bucks?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Stanley
line: The same as the ratio of unicorns to leprechauns.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Okay---

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Andy
line: That's it!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: What---

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Andy
line: Class is canceled, everybody out!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: No wait, what are you doing?!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Andy
line: I'm punishing them.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: No, no, no, wait! Class is not canceled.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Pam
line: HEY! COME ON! Let's listen to Dwight's presentation!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Oscar
line: What--- What are you winking for?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Dwight
line: Zip your lid!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: So, that's... my basic 5 year plan. And after that, who knows?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: Okay. Uh, now, this may seem like an odd question, but...

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: Yeah?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: ...what do you think about Michael Scott?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: He's a very nice man. And he's very well suited for the job he has now.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: This is off the record.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Karen
line: He would be disaster.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: Hey you!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Hey.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: How was your interview?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Pretty good.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: Yeah?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Could have gone better I guess.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: Oh.  I'll put in a good word for you.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Cool. Maybe you should do it sooner rather than later.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: What?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: Daaah, let's just run away together. Let's just run away to Jamaica and live in a bungalow. You have some savings right? You could pay off my debts. It would... be fine. We'd have fun.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: What's... what's the matter? What... what happened in there?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Michael
line: I can't tell you.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: Tell me what?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: You son of a bitch!

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: Jan, this isn't the time, we're in an interview---

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: David Wallace
line: Frankly, it's overdue. Your behavior in the last two years has been completely erratic.

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
speaker: Jan
line: Erratic?

title: The Job (Parts 1&2)
